<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Washington Naval Arms Conference of 1921-1922 resulted in:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">An increase in naval construction</option>
            <option letter="b">Limitations on naval armaments among major powers</option>
            <option letter="c">A military alliance against Germany</option>
            <option letter="d">The creation of the League of Nations</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Washington Naval Conference led to the Five-Power Treaty, which established limits on naval construction and tonnage ratios among the major naval powers (US, Britain, Japan, France, and Italy). This agreement represented a significant diplomatic effort to prevent a naval arms race and reduce military spending in the post-WWI era.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
